text:
(1)
Coney Island Creek at West 20th Street, showing the coal pockets of the Burns Brothers Coal Co. Buildings shown, face on Neptune Ave., which parallels the waters edge. July 1, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, from another angle, showing also P.S. No. 80 on the east side of West 19th Street, just south of Neptune Ave. May 17, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Coney Island Creek - West 20th Street - Brooklyn.
